Is this not a development of the headology themes that we've been
exploring recently? At dx, testing produces Doh! moments that inform
us that our WOE needs to be altered drastically. As we progress away
from dx, using testing to monitor progress gives a continuing sense of
achievement, and so contributes to overall well being. Once you've
plateaued, testing remains a method of disciplining yourself, as well
as answering food questions. It's less relevant as an immediate
motivational tool, because you lose novelty and have to ongoing gains;
but it is nevertheless essential.

